title: Unemployment rate in Hungary 2019
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, containing a total of 21 data points.
In general Unemployment rate has fallen over the Year.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2013 and 2014.
Maximum Unemployment rate, about 11.17 was reported at Year 2010
The lowest Unemployment rate, of value 3.46 was reported at Year 2019
